ul.li: legal - the legal name of the established protected area. Exactly 1 record with this state must exist at a time for a given established or repealed protected area. Visible to all. Editable by admin.

historical - A name that at one point was the legal name for the established protected area, but has since been replaced. Any number of records in this state can exist for a single established or repealed protected area at one time. Visible to all. Not editable by admin.

li.span: Pending - The protected area has not yet received legal designation and is not viewable by the public. Changes are not saved in this state (no change log, no audit log)

ul.li: Established: The protected area has received legal designation, is viewable by the public. Changes are saved in this state.

li.span: Repealed: The protected area has been legally designated as repealed. It is viewable by the public.

ul.li: Deleted - Protected area will never move to established state. All data associated with the protected area is deleted. The protected area id is returned to the protected area id pool. Note - this is not an actual state as no protected area will exist with this state. Confirm with client
